By: Michael Sendivogius
---
In these wicked days, indeed, when virtue and vice are accounted alike,
the ingratitude and unbelief of men keep our Art from appearing openly
before the public gaze. Yet this glorious truth is even now capable of being
apprehended by learned and unlearned persons of virtuous lives, and there
are many persons of all nations now living who have beheld Diana unveiled.
